    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "for some additional context - sometimes the user may not know they are dealing with a bool type. this may occur when performing a groupby on the result of pd.get_dummies, which may return columns of type uint8, but not always. if get_dummies returns a uint16, the issue above is not triggered, and dummies_result.groupby(...).sum() returns int types. if any of the counts in dummies is small enough, the groupby result will be float."
